<subSubSection id="37E2657C4F21FFF4F0FAF928FC196F1F" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph id="7F4736F74F21FFF4F0FAF928FC196F1F" blockId="12.[192,1440,1635,1851]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F21FFF4F0FAF928FE356EFF" author="Gribodo, G." box="[240,416,1731,1755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="102 - 119" refId="ref13273" refString="Gribodo, G. 1892. Contribuzioni imenotterologiche. Sopra alcune specie nuove o poco conosciute di imenotteri antofili (generi Ctenoplectra, Xylocopa, Centris, Psithyrus, Trigona e Bombus). Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana 23: 102 - 119." type="journal article" year="1892">Gribodo (1892)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned this species’ distribution. It is common to observe 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F21FFF4F47BF92FFB726EFF" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[1137,1255,1731,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Apis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanipes">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F21FFF4F47BF92FFB726EFF" box="[1137,1255,1731,1755]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">C. lanipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gathering sand for nest construction along trails of the 
<collectingRegion id="BD3CF8154F21FFF4F2A3F908FC846EDF" box="[681,785,1763,1787]" country="Puerto Rico" name="Guanica" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Guánica</collectingRegion>
dry forest reserve in southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="07EF76674F21FFF4F4C0F90FFACB6EDF" box="[1226,1374,1763,1787]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
. This species may also use preexisting cavities located in various substrates, as occurs in other species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F21FFF4F130F8CFFE4B6F1F" box="[314,478,1828,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Heterocentris">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F21FFF4F130F8CFFE4B6F1F" box="[314,478,1828,1851]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Heterocentris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F21FFF4F1E6F8C8FD026F1F" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[492,663,1827,1851]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref15918" refString="Snelling, R. R. 1984. Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County 347: 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F21FFF4F2A8F8C8FCEA6F1F" author="Vinson, S. &amp; G. W. Frankie &amp; H. J. Williams" box="[674,895,1827,1851]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="109 - 127" refId="ref16548" refString="Vinson, S. B, G. W. Frankie, and H. J. Williams. 1996. Chemical ecology of bees of the genus Centris (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Florida Entomologist 79: 109 - 127." type="journal article" year="1996">Vinson et al. 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
